The paper deals with large scale learning problems and proposes a parallel stochastic algorithm for solving them. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the algorithm proposed in the paper involves parallel processing, which could also make it relevant to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the convergence of the algorithm, which could make it relevant to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of stochastic gradient descent, which is a common technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), making it a possible sub-category as well.
